title: Kletzsch Park Cyclocross
description: Kletzch Park is back for another year, and just like last year we will be featuring one of the longest run ups in the series so ready your legs and lungs for the Pegasus Puker!
course: Course will be a mix of grass and pavement with one long hill run up (the Pegasus Puker)
registration:
Registration opens at 8:00am and closes 20 minutes
before each event. No late or unattached fees. Entry fee
includes USAC insurance ($3) and WCA surcharge ($2).
Riders without a USA Cycling racing license must purchase
a USAC One Day License for $10 or an annual USAC
license.
Held under USA Cycling event permit. USAC rules will
apply.
directions: Take I43 Exit Silver Spring Drive then take Silver Spring Drive North to the Milwaukee River parkway. take the Parkway north for approximately 1.3 miles.
